<LegalLayout title="Delete Your Account" appName="That's So Random!" lastUpdated="June 17, 2026">

  <p>
    You can delete your <strong>That's So Random!</strong> account directly within the app at any time.
    This page is provided by <strong>Refuge &amp; Sword Publishing LLC</strong> in accordance with
    Google Play and Apple App Store data deletion requirements.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>
  <p>Follow these steps from within the app:</p>
  <ol style="margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.5rem; color: var(--midnight-navy);">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Log in to your That's So Random! account.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">From the main screen, tap the <strong>Settings</strong> button.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Scroll to the bottom and tap <strong style="color: #c0392b;">Delete Account</strong>.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Confirm your choice when prompted.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Your account and associated data will be permanently deleted immediately upon confirmation.</p>

  <h2>What Gets Deleted</h2>
  <p>Upon deletion, the following data will be permanently removed from our systems:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your email address and account credentials.</li>
    <li>Your premium purchase record and associated purchase tokens.</li>
    <li>Any account-linked preferences or settings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What Is Retained</h2>
  <p>
    We do not retain personal data after account deletion except where required by law.
    Anonymized or aggregated data that cannot identify you may be retained for operational purposes.
  </p>
  <p>
    If your purchase was processed through the Apple App Store or Google Play, those platforms
    maintain their own transaction records independently of us and subject to their own privacy policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Need Help?</h2>
  <p>
    If you have trouble deleting your account or have questions, contact us at
    <a href="mailto:support@refugeandsword.com" style="color: var(--heritage-gold);">
      support@refugeandsword.com
    </a>.
  </p>

</LegalLayout>
